(l) if: 






 (i) personal property of the person is modified so that it can be used by a disabled person; and
 (ii) the person, the person's partner or a child who is dependent on the person or the person's partner is disabled;
 the part of the value of the property that is attributable to the modifications; 







 ... 


 Relevantly, for the purpose of these applications, the value of a person's investment in a superannuation fund is to be disregarded in calculating the value of that person's assets until the person either reaches pension age or commences to receive a pension or annuity out of the fund.
